How to do it…
We are going to start with some tests that will work just fine. However, if there’s a delay in the response 
for the HTTP calls, they will fail. That is because Cypress has a timeout of 4,000 milliseconds (ms) (4 
seconds), during which it tries the assertion again and again until the assertion passes. What if our 
XHR takes more than 4,000 ms? Let’s try it out in the recipe:
